In Washington, officials from the Department of Homeland Security ruled out terrorism as the cause of the bridge collapse, attributing it to engineering issues.
A school bus with 60 children narrowly avoided falling into the river as the bridge crumbled.
Witness Ramon Houge described the chaotic scene of cars plunging into the water.
The tragic incident in Minneapolis claimed at least six lives, with fears of more casualties.
Rescue efforts were underway as officials urged inspections of similar bridges nationwide to prevent future disasters.
The investigation will focus on reconstructing the bridge to determine the cause.
